nd development in Natural Language Processing. In versions 3.9.3 and prior, `nltk.app.wordnet_app` contains a reflected cross-site scripting issue in the `lookup_...` route. A crafted `lookup_<payload>` URL can inject arbitrary HTML/JavaScript into the response page because attacker-controlled `word` data is reflected into HTML without escaping. This impacts users running the local WordNet Browser server and can lead to script execution in the browser origin of that application. Commit 1c3f799607eeb088cab2491dcf806ae83c29ad8f fixes the issue.","cvss":[{"source":"security-advisories@github.com","type":"Secondary","version":"3.1","vector":"CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:R/S:C/C:L/I:L/A:N","metrics":{"baseScore":6.1,"exploitabilityScore":2.9,"impactScore":2.8},"vendorMetadata":{}}],"epss":[{"cve":"CVE-2026-33230","epss":0.00017,"percentile":0.04026,"date":"2026-05-06"}],"cwes":[{"cve":"CVE-2026-33230","cwe":"CWE-79","source":"security-advisories@github.com","type":"Primary"}]}],"matchDetails":[{"type":"exact-direct-match","matcher":"python-matcher","searchedBy":{"language":"python","namespace":"github:language:python","package":{"name":"nltk","version":"3.9.1"}},"found":{"vulnerabilityID":"GHSA-gfwx-w7gr-fvh7","versionConstraint":"<=3.9.3 (python)"},"fix":{"suggestedVersion":"3.9.4"}}],"artifact":{"id":"f15bf5ac396aa2dc","name":"nltk","version":"3.9.1","type":"python","locations":[{"path":"/requirements.txt","accessPath":"/requirements.txt","annotations":{"evidence":"primary"}}],"language":"python","licenses":[],"cpes":["cpe:2.3:a:python-nltk:python-nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python-nltk:python_nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python_nltk:python-nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python_nltk:python_nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python:python-nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python:python_nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:nltk:python-nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:nltk:python_nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python-nltk:nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python_nltk:nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python:nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:nltk:nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*"],"purl":"pkg:pypi/nltk@3.9.1","upstreams":[]}},{"vulnerability":{"id":"GHSA-69w3-r845-3855","dataSource":"https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-69w3-r845-3855","namespace":"github:language:python","severity":"Medium","urls":["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-1839","https://github.com/huggingface/transformers/commit/03c8082ba4594c9b8d6fe190ca9bed0e5f8ca396","https://huntr.com/bounties/3c77bb97-e493-493d-9a88-c57f5c536485","https://github.com/huggingface/transformers/releases/tag/v5.0.0rc3"],"description":"HuggingFace Transformers allows for arbitrary code execution in the `Trainer` class","cvss":[{"type":"Secondary","version":"3.0","vector":"CVSS:3.0/AV:L/AC:H/PR:N/UI:R/S:U/C:H/I:L/A:H","metrics":{"baseScore":6.5,"exploitabilityScore":1.1,"impactScore":5.5},"vendorMetadata":{}}],"epss":[{"cve":"CVE-2026-1839","epss":0.00016,"percentile":0.03464,"date":"2026-05-06"}],"cwes":[{"cve":"CVE-2026-1839","cwe":"CWE-502","source":"security@huntr.dev","type":"Secondary"}],"fix":{"versions":["5.0.0rc3"],"state":"fixed","available":[{"version":"5.0.0rc3","date":"2026-04-08","kind":"first-observed"}]},"advisories":[],"risk":0.0092},"relatedVulnerabilities":[{"id":"CVE-2026-1839","dataSource":"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-1839","namespace":"nvd:cpe","severity":"High","urls":["https://github.com/huggingface/transformers/commit/03c8082ba4594c9b8d6fe190ca9bed0e5f8ca396","https://huntr.com/bounties/3c77bb97-e493-493d-9a88-c57f5c536485"],"description":"A vulnerability in the HuggingFace Transformers library, specifically in the `Trainer` class, allows for arbitrary code execution. The `_load_rng_state()` method in `src/transformers/trainer.py` at line 3059 calls `torch.load()` without the `weights_only=True` parameter. This issue affects all versions of the library supporting `torch>=2.2` when used with PyTorch versions below 2.6, as the `safe_globals()` context manager provides no protection in these versions. An attacker can exploit this vulnerability by supplying a malicious checkpoint file, such as `rng_state.pth`, which can execute arbitrary code when loaded. The issue is resolved in version v5.0.0rc3.","cvss":[{"source":"nvd@nist.gov","type":"Primary","version":"3.1","vector":"CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:N/UI:R/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H","metrics":{"baseScore":7.8,"exploitabilityScore":1.9,"impactScore":5.9},"vendorMetadata":{}},{"source":"security@huntr.dev","type":"Secondary","version":"3.0","vector":"CVSS:3.0/AV:L/AC:H/PR:N/UI:R/S:U/C:H/I:L/A:H","metrics":{"baseScore":6.5,"exploitabilityScore":1.1,"impactScore":5.5},"vendorMetadata":{}}],"epss":[{"cve":"CVE-2026-1839","epss":0.00016,"percentile":0.03464,"date":"2026-05-06"}],"cwes":[{"cve":"CVE-2026-1839","cwe":"CWE-502","source":"security@huntr.dev","type":"Secondary"}]}],"matchDetails":[{"type":"exact-direct-match","matcher":"python-matcher","searchedBy":{"language":"python","namespace":"github:language:python","package":{"name":"transformers","version":"4.48.0"}},"found":{"vulnerabilityID":"GHSA-69w3-r845-3855","versionConstraint":"<5.0.0rc3 (python)"},"fix":{"suggestedVersion":"5.0.0rc3"}}],"artifact":{"id":"597062d805f321b6","name":"transformers","version":"4.48.0","type":"python","locations":[{"path":"/requirements.txt","accessPath":"/requirements.txt","annotations":{"evidence":"primary"}}],"language":"python","licenses":[],"cpes":["cpe:2.3:a:python-transformers:python-transformers:4.48.0:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python-transformers:python_transformers:4.48.0:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python_transformers:python-transformers:4.48.0:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python_transformers:python_transformers:4.48.0:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python-transformers:transformers:4.48.0:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python_transformers:transformers:4.48.0:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:transformers:python-transformers:4.48.0:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:transformer