"nvd:cpe","severity":"High","urls":["https://huntr.com/bounties/fc69914f-36a9-4c18-8503-10013b39f966"],"description":"A vulnerability in NLTK versions up to and including 3.9.2 allows arbitrary file read via path traversal in multiple CorpusReader classes, including WordListCorpusReader, TaggedCorpusReader, and BracketParseCorpusReader. These classes fail to properly sanitize or validate file paths, enabling attackers to traverse directories and access sensitive files on the server. This issue is particularly critical in scenarios where user-controlled file inputs are processed, such as in machine learning APIs, chatbots, or NLP pipelines. Exploitation of this vulnerability can lead to unauthorized access to sensitive files, including system files, SSH private keys, and API tokens, and may potentially escalate to remote code execution when combined with other vulnerabilities.","cvss":[{"source":"nvd@nist.gov","type":"Primary","version":"3.1","vector":"CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:N/A:N","metrics":{"baseScore":7.5,"exploitabilityScore":3.9,"impactScore":3.6},"vendorMetadata":{}},{"source":"security@huntr.dev","type":"Secondary","version":"3.0","vector":"CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:L/A:L","metrics":{"baseScore":8.6,"exploitabilityScore":3.9,"impactScore":4.8},"vendorMetadata":{}}],"epss":[{"cve":"CVE-2026-0847","epss":0.00076,"percentile":0.22507,"date":"2026-05-06"}],"cwes":[{"cve":"CVE-2026-0847","cwe":"CWE-22","source":"security@huntr.dev","type":"Primary"}]}],"matchDetails":[{"type":"exact-direct-match","matcher":"python-matcher","searchedBy":{"language":"python","namespace":"github:language:python","package":{"name":"nltk","version":"3.9.1"}},"found":{"vulnerabilityID":"GHSA-68j8-pq59-fqgm","versionConstraint":"<=3.9.2 (python)"}}],"artifact":{"id":"f15bf5ac396aa2dc","name":"nltk","version":"3.9.1","type":"python","locations":[{"path":"/requirements.txt","accessPath":"/requirements.txt","annotations":{"evidence":"primary"}}],"language":"python","licenses":[],"cpes":["cpe:2.3:a:python-nltk:python-nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python-nltk:python_nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python_nltk:python-nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python_nltk:python_nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python:python-nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python:python_nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:nltk:python-nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:nltk:python_nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python-nltk:nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python_nltk:nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python:nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:nltk:nltk:3.9.1:*:*:*:*:*:*:*"],"purl":"pkg:pypi/nltk@3.9.1","upstreams":[]}},{"vulnerability":{"id":"GHSA-jjph-296x-mrcr","dataSource":"https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-jjph-296x-mrcr","namespace":"github:language:python","severity":"Medium","urls":["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-3264","https://github.com/huggingface/transformers/commit/0720e206c6ba28887e4d60ef60a6a089f6c1cc76","https://huntr.com/bounties/3c6f7822-9992-476d-8cf0-b0b1623427df","https://github.com/huggingface/transformers/commit/126abe3461762e5fc180e7e614391d1b4ab051ca"],"description":"Transformers vulnerable to ReDoS attack through its get_imports() function","cvss":[{"type":"Secondary","version":"3.0","vector":"CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:L","metrics":{"baseScore":5.3,"exploitabilityScore":3.9,"impactScore":1.5},"vendorMetadata":{}}],"epss":[{"cve":"CVE-2025-3264","epss":0.00096,"percentile":0.26206,"date":"2026-05-06"}],"cwes":[{"cve":"CVE-2025-3264","cwe":"CWE-1333","source":"security@huntr.dev","type":"Secondary"}],"fix":{"versions":["4.51.0"],"state":"fixed","available":[{"version":"4.51.0","date":"2025-07-09","kind":"first-observed"}]},"advisories":[],"risk":0.04944},"relatedVulnerabilities":[{"id":"CVE-2025-3264","dataSource":"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-3264","namespace":"nvd:cpe","severity":"Medium","urls":["https://github.com/huggingface/transformers/commit/0720e206c6ba28887e4d60ef60a6a089f6c1cc76","https://huntr.com/bounties/3c6f7822-9992-476d-8cf0-b0b1623427df"],"description":"A Regular Expression Denial of Service (ReDoS) vulnerability was discovered in the Hugging Face Transformers library, specifically in the `get_imports()` function within `dynamic_module_utils.py`. This vulnerability affects versions 4.49.0 and is fixed in version 4.51.0. The issue arises from a regular expression pattern `\\s*try\\s*:.*?except.*?:` used to filter out try/except blocks from Python code, which can be exploited to cause excessive CPU consumption through crafted input strings due to catastrophic backtracking. This vulnerability can lead to remote code loading disruption, resource exhaustion in model serving, supply chain attack vectors, and development pipeline disruption.","cvss":[{"source":"security@huntr.dev","type":"Secondary","version":"3.0","vector":"CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:L","metrics":{"baseScore":5.3,"exploitabilityScore":3.9,"impactScore":1.5},"vendorMetadata":{}}],"epss":[{"cve":"CVE-2025-3264","epss":0.00096,"percentile":0.26206,"date":"2026-05-06"}],"cwes":[{"cve":"CVE-2025-3264","cwe":"CWE-1333","source":"security@huntr.dev","type":"Secondary"}]}],"matchDetails":[{"type":"exact-direct-match","matcher":"python-matcher","searchedBy":{"language":"python","namespace":"github:language:python","package":{"name":"transformers","version":"4.48.0"}},"found":{"vulnerabilityID":"GHSA-jjph-296x-mrcr","versionConstraint":"<4.51.0 (python)"},"fix":{"suggestedVersion":"4.51.0"}}],"artifact":{"id":"597062d805f321b6","name":"transformers","version":"4.48.0","type":"python","locations":[{"path":"/requirements.txt","accessPath":"/requirements.txt","annotations":{"evidence":"primary"}}],"language":"python","licenses":[],"cpes":["cpe:2.3:a:python-transformers:python-transformers:4.48.0:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python-transformers:python_transformers:4.48.0:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python_transformers:python-transformers:4.48.0:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python_transformers:python_transformers:4.48.0:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python-transformers:transformers:4.48.0:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python_transformers:transformers:4.48.0:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:transformers:python-transformers:4.48.0:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:transformers:python_transformers:4.48.0:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python:python-transformers:4.48.0:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python:python_transformers:4.48.0:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:transformers:transformers:4.48.0:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:python:transformers:4.48.0:*:*:*:*:*:*:*"],"purl":"pkg:pypi/transformers@4.48.0","upstreams":[]}},{"vulnerability":{"id":"GHSA-q2wp-rjmx-x6x9","dataSource":"https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-q2wp-rjmx-x6x9","namespace":"github:language:python","severity":"Medium","urls":["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-3263","https://github.com/huggingface/transformers/commit/0720e206c6ba28887e4d60ef60a6a089f6c1cc76","https://huntr.com/bounties/c7a69150-54f8-4e81-8094-791e7a2a0f29","https://github.com/huggingface/transformers/commit/126abe3461762e5fc180e7e614391d1b4ab051ca"],"description":"Transformers's ReDoS vulnerability in get_configuration_file can lead to catastrophic backtracking","cvss":[{"type":"Secondary","version":"3.0","vector":"CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:L","metrics":{"baseScore":5.3,"exploitabilityScore":3.9,"impactScore":1.5},"vendorMetadata":{}}],"epss":[{"cve":"CVE-2025-3263","epss":0.00096,"percentile":0.26206,"date":"2026-05-06"}],"cwes":[{"cve":"CVE-2025-3263","cwe":"CWE-1333","source":"security@huntr.dev","type":"Secondary"}],"fix":{"versions":["4.51.0"],"state":"fixed","available":[{"version":"4.51.0","date":"2025-07-09","kind":"first-observed"}]},"advisories":[],"risk":0.04944},"relatedVulnerabilities":[{"id":"CVE-2025-3263","dataSource":"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-3263","namespace":"nvd:cpe","severity":"Medium","urls":["https://github.com/huggingface/transformers/commit/0720